  "dataFlow": "External triggers (GitHub push, Linear issue transition, Telegram message, cron schedule, or HTTP POST /api/build) enter the FastAPI backend. Webhooks are HMAC-verified before processing. Authenticated API calls create a BuildSession object (stored in-memory in _sessions dict, persisted to JSON on disk). The session progresses through phases: clone (git clone to app/workspaces/{sid}/), plan (Orchestrator decomposes brief via Claude SDK), generate (claude_agent_sdk executes code changes in workspace), evaluate (second Claude SDK call grades the diff on 4 dimensions), push (git commit + push to origin). All phases stream output lines to session.output_lines, which are consumed by WebSocket /ws/build/{sid} and SSE /api/sessions/{sid}/logs. Terminal status changes are persisted atomically via os.replace(). On completion, Supabase receives gate_checks rows via supabase_log.py. The Autonomy Poller independently polls Linear every 5 minutes, creates sessions for qualifying tickets, and closes tickets on success. Pi-SEO scanner writes JSON findings to .harness/scan-results/, the monitor agent reads them to detect regressions, and the triage engine converts findings to Linear tickets. The MCP server reads .harness/ files and Linear state to answer Claude Desktop tool calls. The Next.js dashboard proxies requests to the FastAPI backend and renders build output in an xterm terminal.",
